pyspark.sql.functions.create_map

Creates a new map column.

Parameters
cols : Column or str
            column names or Columns that are grouped as key-value pairs, e.g. (key1, value1, key2, value2, â€¦).

Examples

df = spark.createDataFrame([("Alice", 2), ("Bob", 5)], ("name", "age"))

df.show()
+-----+---+
| name|age|
+-----+---+
|Alice|  2|
|  Bob|  5|
+-----+---+

df.select(create_map('name', 'age').alias("map")).show()
+------------+
|         map|
+------------+
|{Alice -> 2}|
|  {Bob -> 5}|
+------------+

df.select(create_map([df.name, df.age]).alias("map")).show()
+------------+
|         map|
+------------+
|{Alice -> 2}|
|  {Bob -> 5}|
+------------+
